{"type":"text","timestamp":1780925412296,"sessionID":"ses_158954ad3ffeepM4JX05JFyErC","part":{"id":"prt_ea76d3341001N3biAprffRw8pc","messageID":"msg_ea76d1ba2001xBCDdsfaz2sYYx","sessionID":"ses_158954ad3ffeepM4JX05JFyErC","type":"text","text":"System-spec-kit does store `confidence`, but the active vector decay expression I found uses `importance_weight` without multiplying by `confidence`; that makes OpenLTM’s scalar weighting a possible calibration lesson rather than a missing field.","time":{"start":1780925412161,"end":1780925412293},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0b649874a9002717016a26c3e414c88198a4314bb475259dac","phase":"commentary"}}}}
